glosses.gloss: African tree having an exceedingly thick trunk and fruit that resembles a gourd and has an edible pulp called monkey bread
Adansonia digitata, the baobab, is the most widespread of the Adansonia species, and is native to the African continent.
Genus of big trees (Adansonia) from the mallow family, growing in tropical countries
A tree, Adansonia digitata , native to tropical Africa, having a broad swollen trunk and edible gourd-like hanging fruits.
Baobab is the common name for each of the nine species of tree in the genus Adansonia.
A tree that is known in African folklore as "God's Thumb"
